---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
import CookieBanner from '../components/CookieBanner.astro';
---

<html lang="en">
<head>
    <BaseHead title={`Privacy Policy - ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="Privacy policy for the BuildMC Launcher and Discord app." />
</head>
<body>
    <Header />

    <main>
        <section class="hero">
            <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
            <p>For the BuildMC Launcher and the associated Discord app.</p>
        </section>

        <section class="legal-page">
            <h2>1. Responsible Party</h2>
            <p>
                Jona Gotthardt<br>
                Email: jona.gotthardt@icloud.com
            </p>

            <h2>2. General</h2>
            <p>
                BuildMC Launcher is a desktop application for Minecraft. Privacy and security are our top priorities. This policy explains how personal data is handled.
            </p>

            <h2>3. Discord Rich Presence</h2>
            <p>
                The Discord app displays your activity status (e.g., "BuildMC Launcher – Managing instances") in Discord. It connects locally to the Discord client on your device. No personal data is transmitted via Discord or our servers.
            </p>

            <h2>4. Stored Data</h2>
            <p>
                The launcher stores the following data locally on your device:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Minecraft account information (Microsoft tokens, optional)</li>
                <li>Launcher settings (RAM, Java path, theme)</li>
                <li>Installed instances and mod lists</li>
                <li>SwiftServers login data (API key, stored locally)</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>5. No Data Sharing</h2>
            <p>
                We do not share personal data with third parties. Tokens are used solely for authentication with Microsoft and Minecraft services.
            </p>

            <h2>6. Cookies & Website</h2>
            <p>
                This website does not use tracking cookies. When using the hosting platform (Cloudflare), technical data such as IP address and browser information may be processed to deliver the site.
            </p>

            <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
            <p>
                You have the right to access, rectify, erase, and restrict processing of your data. Since data is stored locally, you can delete it directly on your device at any time.
            </p>
        </section>
    </main>

    <Footer />
    <CookieBanner />
</body>
</html>
